article.description: Allie Quigley had 24 points and nine rebounds to lead DePaul (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No.23 AP) to a 91-80 overtime win over St. John's on Tuesday night.
article.headline: DePaul outscores St. John's 14-3 in overtime
article.linkText: St. John's makes No. 22 DePaul work OT for win
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Allie Quigley had 24 points and nine rebounds to lead DePaul (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No.23 AP) to a 91-80 overtime win over St. John's on Tuesday night.

With DePaul down two with 3 seconds left in regulation, Quigley made two free throws to send the game into overtime. The Blue Demons (13-3, 2-1 Big East) outscored the Red Storm 14-3 in the extra session.

Five Blue Demons scored in the double digits. Ciara Johnson had 16, Caprice Smith had 14, Natasha Williams had 11 and Deirdre Naughton finished with 10 points.

St. John's (10-6, 1-2) led 44-42 at halftime, but DePaul used a 15-2 run to start the second half to take an 11-point lead before St. John's rallied. Trailing 67-60, the Red Storm went on an 8-0 spurt capped by Sky Lindsay's 3-pointer with 7:27 left.

The final seven minutes of the second half were back-and-forth as neither team led by more than two points with the scored being tied on three occasions.

Kelly McManmon led the Red Storm with 19 points. Lindsay added 17.
